On our channel we create Ğ° trailer mashups â–·
Also known as recut trailers, involve collecting multiple pieces of film footage from one or multiple movies and Add Our Own Dialogues To Make A New And Fresh Story, editing them to create a new trailer. Trailer mashups are often created for a movie that does not exist now or to change the genre of an existing film. These are derivative works as defined by the United States Copyright Act 17 U.S.C. Â§ 101, and as such, may find protection from copyright claims under the doctrine of fair use.

The trailer mashups are not only a user generated form of digital creativity but a way to create anticipation for future releases, working in tandem with current movie trailers. Movie trailers are designed to give minimal plot detail and to create hype and anticipation. Fan made trailer mashups allow the audience to perform their own cinematic spin on current movie footage. This allows the trailer to focus on a specific actor or portion of the film. It could even change the plot ocr genre of the film entirely.

This video is a parody DUE to its derivative/ transformative nature this video is covered as a Fair Use of material.

Jiiva speech Thalaivar Thambi Thalaimaiyil trailer launch.
Jiiva speech TTT trailer launch.
Jiiva speech in Thalaivar Thambi Thalaimaiyil pre release event. 

Presenting Jiiva speech TTT movie. Thalaivar Thambi Thalaimaiyil trailer launch happened in Chennai today.

Thalaivar Thambi Thalaimaiyil is an s an 2026 Indian Tamil-language film written and directed by Nithish Sahadev. The film stars Jiiva,Thambi Ramaiya, Ilavarasu, Prathana Nathan, Jensen Dhivakar, Jaiwanth, Sarjin Kumar, Rajesh Pandian, Subash Kannan, Amith Mohan, Anuraj OB, Sharath, Savithri & Others. The film has music composed by Vishnu Vijay, cinematography handled by Bablu Aju and editing by Arjune Babu. 

Thalaivar Thambi Thalaimaiyil is scheduled to release in theatres worldwide on 15 January 2026.

You asked for it. The path to 6 hunters continues. Now we take on 4 hunters. The hunters are back and better than ever. Will we move on to 5?

â½ Instagram - @dreamwastaken
â½ Snapchat - @dream

BadBoyHalo:   @thesaintsofgames 
George:    @GeorgeNotFound 
Sapnap:    @Sapnap 
Antfrost: @Antfrost

Version: 1.21.11

We decided to call this series Minecraft Manhunt. This video is a different rendition of it, where there is FOUR hunters. The 6th rendition of the 4 hunters series, the revival...

This is a new Minecraft but, 1.21.11 challenge that we have decided to try. I try to beat the game, while my friends George and Sapnap and BadBoyHalo and Antfrost try to prevent me from doing it. It's a race, and it's super intense and we had a lot of laughs. I love doing these challenges.

snippet.title: Rishtey (Official Music Video) | Jass Bajwa | Punjabi Song 2026
snippet.description:
Jass Bajwa presents the official music video of Rishtey. It is a touching Punjabi song that shows the deep bond between a daughter and her family. As she gets ready to leave her parentsâ€™ home after marriage, memories of childhood, siblings, and family moments come rushing back.

The song captures her love, fear, and pain of leaving the house where she grew up. She remembers small fights, shared laughter, and the comfort of seeing her parents every day. Before starting her new life, she makes emotional requests to her brother and sister, showing how strongly she is connected to her family. Rishtey beautifully reflects love, memories, and the strength it takes to move forward while keeping family close to the heart.

snippet.title: Teri Dulhan Sajaoongi | Barsaat | Alka Yagnik | Kailash Khair | Nadeem Shravan
snippet.description:
â€œTeri Dulhan Sajaoongiâ€ is a soulful romantic track from the film Barsaat, beautifully sung by Alka Yagnik and Kailash Kher. Composed by the legendary duo Nadeemâ€“Shravan, the song captures pure love, devotion, and the heartfelt promise of a bride preparing herself for her beloved.

Movie: a sublime love story- Barsaat (2005)
Featuring: Bobby Deol, Priyanka Chopra, and Bipasha Basu
Song: Saajan Saajan Teri Dulhan Sajaoongi 
Singers: Alka Yagnik, Kailash Kher
Music: Nadeem Shravan
Lyrics: Sameer
Produced & Director: Suneel Darshan
Production : Shree Krishna International
Music Lable: Shree Krishna Audio


Song Lyrics:

Hazaro Manzilein Hogi Hazaro Karwaa Honge
Nigaahein Humko Dhundegi Na Jaane Hum Kaha Honge
Saajan Saajan Saajan Mere Saajan Mere Saajan
Teri Dulhan Sajaungi Teri Dulhan Sajaungi
Teri Dulhan Sajaungi
Wada Diya Tujhe Jo Bhi Wada Diya Tujhe Main
Wo Wada Nibhaungi Main Woh Wada Nibhaaungi
Saajan Saajan Saajan Mere Saajan Mere Saajan
Teri Dulhan Sajaungi Teri Dulhan Sajaungi

a common theme in Islamic and Sufi poetry, reflecting the Quranic and Hadith teachings that poverty can bring hardship and tests from God, but also immense reward and spiritual closeness to Allah

Key Islamic Concepts in the Theme:
Sabr (Patience) & Tawakkul (Trust in God): The core message is that the poor must be patient and rely on Allah, who promises to reward them in the hereafter (Akhirah).
** Dunya (Worldly Life) is Temporary:** Islam teaches that this life is a test, and worldly status, wealth, or enmity doesn't matter in the eyes of God.
** Zakat & Sadaqah (Charity):** The emphasis on helping the poor shows their importance, as giving charity cleanses the wealth of the giver and elevates the status of the poor. 
Common Story Archetypes (Not one single story):
Prophet Ayub (Job): His story is a prime example of immense suffering and poverty, yet he remained patient and never blamed God, eventually receiving blessings.
Prophet Muhammad (PBUH) in Mecca: He and his companions faced severe poverty and persecution (dushman zamana), relying solely on Allah.
Sufi Saints: Many Sufi stories feature ascetics who willingly embraced poverty (faqr) to get closer to God, seeing wealth as a distraction.

a common theme in Islamic and Sufi poetry, reflecting the Quranic and Hadith teachings that poverty can bring hardship and tests from God, but also immense reward and spiritual closeness to Allah

Key Islamic Concepts in the Theme:
Sabr (Patience) & Tawakkul (Trust in God): The core message is that the poor must be patient and rely on Allah, who promises to reward them in the hereafter (Akhirah).
** Dunya (Worldly Life) is Temporary:** Islam teaches that this life is a test, and worldly status, wealth, or enmity doesn't matter in the eyes of God.
** Zakat & Sadaqah (Charity):** The emphasis on helping the poor shows their importance, as giving charity cleanses the wealth of the giver and elevates the status of the poor. 
Common Story Archetypes (Not one single story):
Prophet Ayub (Job): His story is a prime example of immense suffering and poverty, yet he remained patient and never blamed God, eventually receiving blessings.
Prophet Muhammad (PBUH) in Mecca: He and his companions faced severe poverty and persecution (dushman zamana), relying solely on Allah.
Sufi Saints: Many Sufi stories feature ascetics who willingly embraced poverty (faqr) to get closer to God, seeing wealth as a distraction.
